stylometry: A decision tree allows you to look at probabilities and monetary value associated with each decision you would make in business. If a company is looking to buy some equipment, or a building, but it does not know which kind would be best invested in then a decision tree might be a possible way to assess this. It has nodes, probability centers, and decision centers, and when you reach the end you can find your expected monetary value and figure which is the best decision monetarily and risk wise. If a company is looking at buying a new warehouse but is not sure which why the market will swing a decision tree could be used. The probability there is a not good market and a good market will be taken into account, the expense monetarily, and the amount of money made on the investment with each type of market. Going through a decision tree of this model and help us decide which would be our best decision even with a bit of risk involved in not know what the market might do.
